1
00:00:00,834 --> 00:00:06,334
I couldn’t sleep on my back for a month after I got out from the whipping

2
00:00:09,626 --> 00:00:15,083
That was because of the pain, since my
back became striped from the whipping marks

3
00:00:17,125 --> 00:00:22,584
And because of the force of the beating, swelling would appear on my back

4
00:00:24,167 --> 00:00:25,834
There would be swelling where I was beaten

5
00:00:27,542 --> 00:00:29,584
It would stay for a month or more until it healed

6
00:00:32,209 --> 00:00:34,709
Interviewer: Did it leave scars on your body?

7
00:00:34,792 --> 00:00:37,959
No, there were no scars

8
00:00:39,250 --> 00:00:40,792
Interviewer: And what about the psychological harm?

9
00:00:40,792 --> 00:00:47,250
How long did you keep seeing nightmares when you slept?

10
00:00:48,459 --> 00:00:49,918
They lasted until we were freed

11
00:00:52,083 --> 00:00:56,876
Those nightmares kept haunting me until we were freed

12
00:00:58,042 --> 00:00:59,250
Interviewer: What did you dream about?

13
00:00:59,250 --> 00:01:01,751
I dreamed about many things

14
00:01:02,918 --> 00:01:06,709
Not every day did we see those dreams

15
00:01:10,125 --> 00:01:13,959
Sometimes when you’re sitting outside

16
00:01:15,459 --> 00:01:17,667
I felt like a shell was going to fall on me

17
00:01:18,042 --> 00:01:21,500
Or that they were coming to kill me or detain me

18
00:01:21,876 --> 00:01:25,250
And I would stay afraid, thinking about my time in prison

19
00:01:26,125 --> 00:01:30,751
When something happened, I feared they would arrest me and kill me
